#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.0"
msgid "71. Sahadhammikasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.71\">Monks’ Confession 71: the training rule on "
"legitimately</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.141
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.141\""
">Vin.4.141</a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.71.1\">Bu-Pc.71.1</a><a class"
"=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.36\">BD.3.36</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1302</a>At one "
"time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo anācāraṃ ācarati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Channa was misbehaving."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks told him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.4"
msgid "“māvuso channa, evarūpaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "“Channa, don’t do that;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.5"
msgid "Netaṃ kappatī”ti."
msgstr "it’s not allowable,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.6"
msgid "So evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "and he would reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.7"
msgid ""
"“na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is a "
"competent expert on the monastic law.”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.8"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1303</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.9"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.10"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vakkhati—"
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Channa, when legitimately corrected by the monks, say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.11"
msgid ""
"‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is a "
"competent expert on the monastic law’?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.12"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vadesi—"
msgstr "“Is it true, Channa, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.13"
msgid ""
"‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.16"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ "
"vakkhasi—"
msgstr "Foolish man, when legitimately corrected by the monks, how can you say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.17"
msgid ""
"‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is a "
"competent expert on the monastic law’?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.20"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vadeyya—‘na tāvāhaṃ, "
"āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ "
"vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’ti, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.3.37\">BD.3.37</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1304</a>‘If a monk, when "
"legitimately corrected by the monks, says, “I won’t practice this training "
"rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is a competent expert on the monastic "
"law,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:1.1.21"
msgid ""
"Sikkhamānena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā aññātabbaṃ paripucchitabbaṃ "
"paripañhitabbaṃ. Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Monks, a monk who is training should understand, should enquire, should "
"investigate. This is the proper procedure.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.71.2\"></a><a "
"class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.71.2.1\">Bu-Pc.71.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1305</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhūhīti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1306</a><term>By the monks</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.7"
msgid "aññehi bhikkhūhi."
msgstr "<gloss>by other monks.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.8"
msgid "Sahadhammikaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1307</a><term>Legitimately</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.9"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavatā paññattaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ etaṃ sahadhammikaṃ nāma."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>whatever training rule has been laid down by the Master—this is "
"called “legitimately.”"

#. HTML: </b>
#. VAR: ti → imāni padāni s1-3 potthakesu na 
#. VAR: vadeti → vadeyyāti (bj, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.10"
msgid "Tena vuccamāno evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "When corrected in regard to this, he says,"

#. VAR: byattaṃ → imāni padāni s1-3 potthakesu na
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"“na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who’s a "
"competent expert on the monastic law.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.1.12"
msgid ""
"Paṇḍitaṃ byattaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ paripucchāmīti bhaṇati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he says, “I’ll question one who’s wise/one who’s competent/one who’s "
"intelligent/one who’s learned/an expounder of the Teaching,” he commits an "
"offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, pts-vp-pli4.142
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.71.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.71.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1308</a>If the one who corrects him is "
"fully ordained, and he perceives him as fully ordained, and he says such a "
"thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.2"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.38\">BD.3.38</a> If the one who corrects "
"him is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he says such a thing, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.3"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the one who corrects him is fully ordained, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\""
"Vin.4.142\">Vin.4.142</a> but he does not perceive him as fully ordained, "
"and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.4"
msgid "Apaññattena vuccamāno—"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1309</a>If he is corrected about something that has "
"not been laid down:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.5"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ na sallekhāya na dhutatthāya na pāsādikatāya na apacayāya na "
"vīriyārambhāya saṃvattatī”ti evaṃ vadeti, “na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ "
"sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paṇḍitaṃ "
"medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ paripucchāmī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"“This isn’t conducive to the erasing of defilements/to ascetic practices/to "
"being inspiring/to a reduction in things/to being energetic,” and he says, “"
"I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who’s "
"competent/who’s an expert on the monastic law/who’s wise/who’s "
"intelligent/who’s learned/who’s an expounder of the Teaching,” he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampannena paññattena vā apaññattena vā vuccamāno—"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1310</a>If he is corrected by one who is not fully "
"ordained about something that has or has not been laid down:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.7"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ na sallekhāya na dhutatthāya na pāsādikatāya na apacayāya na "
"vīriyārambhāya saṃvattatī”ti evaṃ vadeti, “na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ "
"sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paṇḍitaṃ "
"medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ paripucchāmī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"“This isn’t conducive to the erasing of defilements/to ascetic practices/to "
"being inspiring/to a reduction in things/to being energetic,” and he says, “"
"I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who’s "
"competent/who’s an expert on the monastic law/who’s wise/who’s "
"intelligent/who’s learned/who’s an expounder of the Teaching,” he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If the one who corrects him is not fully ordained, but he perceives him "
"as fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.9"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the one who corrects him is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, "
"he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.10"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the one who corrects him is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive "
"him as fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.11"
msgid "Sikkhamānenāti"
msgstr "<hr><p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1311</a><term>Who is training</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.12"
msgid "sikkhitukāmena."
msgstr "<gloss>who wants to train.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.13"
msgid "Aññātabbanti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1312</a><term>Should understand</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.14"
msgid "jānitabbaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>should find out.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.15"
msgid "Paripucchitabbanti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.39\">BD.3.39</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1313</a><term>Should enquire</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.16"
msgid "“idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ;"
msgstr "<gloss>should ask, “Venerable, how is this?"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.17"
msgid "imassa vā kvattho”ti?"
msgstr "What’s the meaning of this?”</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.18"
msgid "Paripañhitabbanti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1314</a><term>Should investigate</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.19"
msgid "cintetabbaṃ tulayitabbaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>should reflect, should weigh up.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.20"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1315</a><term>This is the proper procedure</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.2.21"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "<gloss>this is the right method.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc15
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.71.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.71.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1316</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.3.2"
msgid "“jānissāmi sikkhissāmī”ti bhaṇati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he says, “I will find out and I will train;” if he is insane; if he is "
"the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc71:2.3.3"
msgid "Sahadhammikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1317</a>The first rule, the "
"training rule on legitimately, is finished.</p>"
